WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.800 align:middle line:90%


00:00:00.800 --> 00:00:03.000 align:middle line:10%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:03.000 --> 00:00:08.000 align:middle line:90%


00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:09.920 align:middle line:84%
>> Hi, it's James here
from "Food Matters."

00:00:09.920 --> 00:00:11.378 align:middle line:84%
And today, we're
going to be taking

00:00:11.378 --> 00:00:15.350 align:middle line:84%
a special spiritual discourse
into understanding more

00:00:15.350 --> 00:00:17.420 align:middle line:84%
about what it means
to live a deeply

00:00:17.420 --> 00:00:22.520 align:middle line:84%
compassionate, loving,
heart-centered and service-led

00:00:22.520 --> 00:00:26.430 align:middle line:84%
life with none other than
Sadhvi Bhagawatiji Saraswatiji.

00:00:26.430 --> 00:00:29.940 align:middle line:90%


00:00:29.940 --> 00:00:31.730 align:middle line:90%
>> Hello, Sadhvi.

00:00:31.730 --> 00:00:33.720 align:middle line:84%
>> It's wonderful to
be with you, James.

00:00:33.720 --> 00:00:35.390 align:middle line:90%
>> Likewise.

00:00:35.390 --> 00:00:40.400 align:middle line:84%
Your journey into
becoming a swami, per se,

00:00:40.400 --> 00:00:45.080 align:middle line:84%
is not a normal sort
of journey for most.

00:00:45.080 --> 00:00:48.530 align:middle line:84%
Can you explain to me the
sort of origins of your story

00:00:48.530 --> 00:00:52.670 align:middle line:90%
and how this began for you?

00:00:52.670 --> 00:00:53.570 align:middle line:90%
>> Sure.

00:00:53.570 --> 00:00:56.030 align:middle line:84%
Well, first of all,
it's really important

00:00:56.030 --> 00:01:02.600 align:middle line:84%
to realize that although there
is a story and there is a plot,

00:01:02.600 --> 00:01:07.970 align:middle line:84%
and I'm happy to share it
with you, that at the core

00:01:07.970 --> 00:01:11.420 align:middle line:90%
it's a story of grace.

00:01:11.420 --> 00:01:20.030 align:middle line:84%
And so as you hear it, realize
that what it is that's going on

00:01:20.030 --> 00:01:25.880 align:middle line:84%
is a heart and a
life that's being

00:01:25.880 --> 00:01:32.550 align:middle line:84%
cracked open to the presence
of more and more grace.

00:01:32.550 --> 00:01:35.210 align:middle line:84%
And that's really important
because people these days

00:01:35.210 --> 00:01:40.760 align:middle line:84%
think much more in terms
of I'm going to do it.

00:01:40.760 --> 00:01:43.640 align:middle line:84%
And actually, there's
this incredible power

00:01:43.640 --> 00:01:48.050 align:middle line:84%
in the universe, an incredible
intelligence in the universe,

00:01:48.050 --> 00:01:52.460 align:middle line:84%
a wisdom in the universe, an
energy in the universe that

00:01:52.460 --> 00:01:55.370 align:middle line:90%
is there for us.

00:01:55.370 --> 00:01:59.300 align:middle line:84%
And we just have to
open ourselves to it.

00:01:59.300 --> 00:02:04.310 align:middle line:90%
So I was 25.

00:02:04.310 --> 00:02:09.800 align:middle line:84%
I was in the midst of a
PhD program in psychology.

00:02:09.800 --> 00:02:14.060 align:middle line:84%
I had graduated from
Stanford, undergrad, and was

00:02:14.060 --> 00:02:17.690 align:middle line:90%
doing a PhD in psychology.

00:02:17.690 --> 00:02:22.430 align:middle line:84%
I was not consciously
seeking or searching,

00:02:22.430 --> 00:02:26.600 align:middle line:84%
which is incredibly embarrassing
to admit 23 years later, when

00:02:26.600 --> 00:02:30.830 align:middle line:84%
my ego would love to
say, since childhood

00:02:30.830 --> 00:02:33.500 align:middle line:84%
I was aware that there
must be something deeper.

00:02:33.500 --> 00:02:38.510 align:middle line:84%
And I was praying for it
and meditating upon it.

00:02:38.510 --> 00:02:40.520 align:middle line:90%
But that isn't my story.

00:02:40.520 --> 00:02:44.960 align:middle line:84%
I had no idea that
something else existed.

00:02:44.960 --> 00:02:48.080 align:middle line:84%
In this culture, in
this world, we're

00:02:48.080 --> 00:02:51.800 align:middle line:84%
really kind of
indoctrinated to believe

00:02:51.800 --> 00:02:57.620 align:middle line:84%
that a successful life
means get a good education,

00:02:57.620 --> 00:02:59.750 align:middle line:84%
get a good career,
make a lot of money,

00:02:59.750 --> 00:03:01.910 align:middle line:84%
look the right way
in the right clothes,

00:03:01.910 --> 00:03:03.590 align:middle line:84%
get invited to
the right parties,

00:03:03.590 --> 00:03:07.340 align:middle line:84%
vacation at the right
resorts, and boom, success.

00:03:07.340 --> 00:03:10.960 align:middle line:90%
And so I had those things.

00:03:10.960 --> 00:03:15.360 align:middle line:90%


00:03:15.360 --> 00:03:26.960 align:middle line:84%
I went to India with a
backpack because the person

00:03:26.960 --> 00:03:30.320 align:middle line:84%
I was traveling with
wanted to go to India.

00:03:30.320 --> 00:03:32.570 align:middle line:90%
So it wasn't even my choice.

00:03:32.570 --> 00:03:37.580 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't even that I woke
up one day and said India.

00:03:37.580 --> 00:03:41.210 align:middle line:84%
My typical vacation
spot was Europe.

00:03:41.210 --> 00:03:43.040 align:middle line:90%
But India, OK.

00:03:43.040 --> 00:03:45.750 align:middle line:84%
Well, I only even agreed
to go to India-- again,

00:03:45.750 --> 00:03:50.570 align:middle line:84%
as embarrassing because it
is almost 25 years later--

00:03:50.570 --> 00:03:52.970 align:middle line:84%
I only agreed to
go because I was

00:03:52.970 --> 00:03:55.610 align:middle line:90%
a staunch, staunch vegetarian.

00:03:55.610 --> 00:03:56.930 align:middle line:90%
I still am.

00:03:56.930 --> 00:04:02.930 align:middle line:84%
And trying to negotiate
broths, and sauces, and stocks,

00:04:02.930 --> 00:04:05.330 align:middle line:84%
and things like that
in languages you

00:04:05.330 --> 00:04:07.790 align:middle line:84%
don't speak, in restaurants
all over the world,

00:04:07.790 --> 00:04:14.000 align:middle line:84%
is very difficult. And so
when India was suggested,

00:04:14.000 --> 00:04:16.760 align:middle line:84%
the one thing I realized
was, well, at least

00:04:16.760 --> 00:04:19.490 align:middle line:90%
I'll be able to eat happily.

00:04:19.490 --> 00:04:25.700 align:middle line:84%
And on the airplane from
San Francisco to Delhi,

00:04:25.700 --> 00:04:30.390 align:middle line:84%
I had this moment in which I
realized this makes no sense.

00:04:30.390 --> 00:04:31.700 align:middle line:90%
This is crazy.

00:04:31.700 --> 00:04:34.040 align:middle line:84%
I'm flying halfway
around the world,

00:04:34.040 --> 00:04:37.400 align:middle line:84%
to a country I know
nothing about, that I'm not

00:04:37.400 --> 00:04:44.462 align:middle line:84%
interested in, only because
they know what vegetarian means.

00:04:44.462 --> 00:04:45.920 align:middle line:84%
I'm not going to
find that there is

00:04:45.920 --> 00:04:49.040 align:middle line:84%
chicken stock, or fish
sauce, or egg yolks,

00:04:49.040 --> 00:04:51.650 align:middle line:90%
or something in my food.

00:04:51.650 --> 00:04:53.690 align:middle line:84%
Well, that was true
in the Bay Area.

00:04:53.690 --> 00:04:56.990 align:middle line:84%
I already was living in a
place where that was true.

00:04:56.990 --> 00:05:00.080 align:middle line:84%
I didn't have to fly across
the world for a good vegetarian

00:05:00.080 --> 00:05:00.950 align:middle line:90%
meal.

00:05:00.950 --> 00:05:06.980 align:middle line:84%
So even though I was not
religious, I was raised Jewish,

00:05:06.980 --> 00:05:12.020 align:middle line:84%
and had and still have a
very deep cultural connection

00:05:12.020 --> 00:05:14.070 align:middle line:90%
to the Jewish people.

00:05:14.070 --> 00:05:16.340 align:middle line:90%
But it never was about God.

00:05:16.340 --> 00:05:18.200 align:middle line:84%
I never had any
connection with God.

00:05:18.200 --> 00:05:19.970 align:middle line:84%
I never had any
awareness of God.

00:05:19.970 --> 00:05:24.390 align:middle line:84%
I never had any
relationship with God.

00:05:24.390 --> 00:05:27.740 align:middle line:84%
But I did have a
very deep belief

00:05:27.740 --> 00:05:32.080 align:middle line:84%
in what I used to call
the, capital P, Planner.

00:05:32.080 --> 00:05:32.940 align:middle line:90%
I was a scientist.

00:05:32.940 --> 00:05:37.160 align:middle line:84%
I had spent time in bio labs,
and chem labs, and stuff.

00:05:37.160 --> 00:05:40.100 align:middle line:84%
And you've got yourself
a Bunsen burner.

00:05:40.100 --> 00:05:41.750 align:middle line:90%
You've got yourself a crucible.

00:05:41.750 --> 00:05:47.770 align:middle line:84%
And nine times out of
10, nothing happens.

00:05:47.770 --> 00:05:49.060 align:middle line:90%
Sometimes you get a bad smell.

00:05:49.060 --> 00:05:51.010 align:middle line:90%
Sometimes you get some smoke.

00:05:51.010 --> 00:05:56.560 align:middle line:84%
But the idea that
somehow all of this

00:05:56.560 --> 00:05:59.410 align:middle line:84%
happened randomly, when
we couldn't recreate it

00:05:59.410 --> 00:06:01.810 align:middle line:84%
in a science lab knowing
everything we do,

00:06:01.810 --> 00:06:03.410 align:middle line:90%
didn't make sense to me.

00:06:03.410 --> 00:06:08.890 align:middle line:84%
So I always had faith that
there was a, capital P, Planner,

00:06:08.890 --> 00:06:11.680 align:middle line:84%
who understood the,
capital P, Plan.

00:06:11.680 --> 00:06:14.260 align:middle line:84%
I didn't understand
it, but that was OK.

00:06:14.260 --> 00:06:17.280 align:middle line:84%
And so when I was
on the airplane,

00:06:17.280 --> 00:06:20.290 align:middle line:84%
I thought this makes
no sense, which

00:06:20.290 --> 00:06:24.670 align:middle line:84%
means that there must be
a purpose that I'm just

00:06:24.670 --> 00:06:27.400 align:middle line:90%
not aware of.

00:06:27.400 --> 00:06:29.290 align:middle line:90%
Because I wasn't a wanderer.

00:06:29.290 --> 00:06:32.680 align:middle line:84%
I wasn't someone who just
kind of went somewhere

00:06:32.680 --> 00:06:34.090 align:middle line:90%
for no reason.

00:06:34.090 --> 00:06:36.340 align:middle line:90%
I was a doer.

00:06:36.340 --> 00:06:41.260 align:middle line:84%
And so I went through Stanford,
for example, undergrad in three

00:06:41.260 --> 00:06:43.010 align:middle line:90%
years, instead of four years.

00:06:43.010 --> 00:06:46.150 align:middle line:84%
And so if you're going
to do it, just do it.

00:06:46.150 --> 00:06:49.940 align:middle line:84%
So I wasn't the type
who just wandered.

00:06:49.940 --> 00:06:54.680 align:middle line:84%
So somewhere over the
Pacific I realized

00:06:54.680 --> 00:06:57.150 align:middle line:90%
there is a reason I'm going.

00:06:57.150 --> 00:07:01.550 align:middle line:84%
And I don't know it, which means
I need to keep my heart open.

00:07:01.550 --> 00:07:05.140 align:middle line:84%
And if I can't
keep my heart open,

00:07:05.140 --> 00:07:08.500 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to come
back to California

00:07:08.500 --> 00:07:11.650 align:middle line:84%
because even though I've taken
a semester off from my program,

00:07:11.650 --> 00:07:14.570 align:middle line:84%
there's still a lot of things I
could do that would be useful,

00:07:14.570 --> 00:07:17.950 align:middle line:84%
and beneficial, and not just
wandering around a country I

00:07:17.950 --> 00:07:19.610 align:middle line:90%
have no interest in.

00:07:19.610 --> 00:07:21.990 align:middle line:90%
So I have to keep my heart open.

00:07:21.990 --> 00:07:27.700 align:middle line:84%
And that proved to be the best
vow I've ever taken in my life

00:07:27.700 --> 00:07:34.270 align:middle line:90%
because about a weekish later--

00:07:34.270 --> 00:07:35.800 align:middle line:84%
we were in Delhi
a couple of days.

00:07:35.800 --> 00:07:39.340 align:middle line:84%
And I opened a guidebook in
Delhi, a big "Lonely Planet"

00:07:39.340 --> 00:07:43.540 align:middle line:84%
guidebook, and said,
Rishikesh, just like that.

00:07:43.540 --> 00:07:44.650 align:middle line:90%
It was close to Delhi.

00:07:44.650 --> 00:07:46.150 align:middle line:90%
I was a nature person.

00:07:46.150 --> 00:07:47.080 align:middle line:90%
There's mountains.

00:07:47.080 --> 00:07:49.780 align:middle line:90%
There's river, yoga classes.

00:07:49.780 --> 00:07:53.050 align:middle line:84%
It was close enough to Delhi
that we could go and sort

00:07:53.050 --> 00:07:55.690 align:middle line:84%
of plan out the rest
of the trip from there.

00:07:55.690 --> 00:08:00.370 align:middle line:84%
It seemed very nice, and
clean, and natural beauty.

00:08:00.370 --> 00:08:06.040 align:middle line:90%


00:08:06.040 --> 00:08:09.100 align:middle line:84%
So we go to Rishikesh
a couple of days later.

00:08:09.100 --> 00:08:12.910 align:middle line:84%
And of all the hotels
in Rishikesh-- now,

00:08:12.910 --> 00:08:16.240 align:middle line:84%
where our ashram
Parmarth Niketan is--

00:08:16.240 --> 00:08:18.160 align:middle line:90%
now there's lots of hotels.

00:08:18.160 --> 00:08:22.870 align:middle line:84%
But at that time, 23 years
ago, all of the hotels

00:08:22.870 --> 00:08:27.010 align:middle line:84%
were on the main downtown
side of Rishikesh

00:08:27.010 --> 00:08:29.650 align:middle line:84%
or up in the northern
part of Rishikesh,

00:08:29.650 --> 00:08:32.080 align:middle line:90%
called Lakshman Jhula.

00:08:32.080 --> 00:08:36.010 align:middle line:84%
Where our ashram is
there was only one hotel.

00:08:36.010 --> 00:08:39.260 align:middle line:84%
And that hotel was
called the Green Hotel.

00:08:39.260 --> 00:08:41.620 align:middle line:84%
And in Delhi, I had
chosen that hotel

00:08:41.620 --> 00:08:44.590 align:middle line:84%
because I was an ardent
environmentalist.

00:08:44.590 --> 00:08:48.700 align:middle line:84%
And it never occurred to me that
the hotel was named Green Hotel

00:08:48.700 --> 00:08:50.380 align:middle line:84%
just because its
walls were painted

00:08:50.380 --> 00:08:52.210 align:middle line:90%
this kind of pastely green.

00:08:52.210 --> 00:08:55.450 align:middle line:84%
But I thought Green
Hotel, OK, great.

00:08:55.450 --> 00:09:02.020 align:middle line:84%
And get to the
hotel, drop our bags.

00:09:02.020 --> 00:09:08.030 align:middle line:84%
And I said, I'm going to go
put my feet in the river.

00:09:08.030 --> 00:09:08.830 align:middle line:90%
I was hot.

00:09:08.830 --> 00:09:11.610 align:middle line:90%
I was tired.

00:09:11.610 --> 00:09:15.610 align:middle line:84%
Just-- I'm going to go
put my feet in the river.

00:09:15.610 --> 00:09:17.970 align:middle line:90%
And I go down.

00:09:17.970 --> 00:09:26.860 align:middle line:84%
And before my feet
even touched the water,

00:09:26.860 --> 00:09:30.370 align:middle line:84%
I looked out over
this river that's

00:09:30.370 --> 00:09:31.960 align:middle line:84%
sacred, that's the
Mother Goddess.

00:09:31.960 --> 00:09:34.330 align:middle line:90%
But I didn't know that.

00:09:34.330 --> 00:09:36.830 align:middle line:84%
I didn't even know
that at the time.

00:09:36.830 --> 00:09:40.070 align:middle line:90%
I just knew river.

00:09:40.070 --> 00:09:41.290 align:middle line:90%
And I stand there.

00:09:41.290 --> 00:09:43.090 align:middle line:90%
And I look out over the river.

00:09:43.090 --> 00:09:44.860 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly, in
that moment, it was

00:09:44.860 --> 00:09:49.900 align:middle line:84%
like a veil was ripped
off, not just my eyes,

00:09:49.900 --> 00:09:55.990 align:middle line:84%
but off of every way of knowing
that I had, off of every sense

00:09:55.990 --> 00:10:02.800 align:middle line:84%
organ, off of my brain, off of
my mind, off of my identity,

00:10:02.800 --> 00:10:04.930 align:middle line:84%
as though this veil
was just pulled off.

00:10:04.930 --> 00:10:10.270 align:middle line:90%
And suddenly I could see.

00:10:10.270 --> 00:10:11.560 align:middle line:90%
But not just with my eyes.

00:10:11.560 --> 00:10:16.780 align:middle line:84%
I could see you with
my entire being.

00:10:16.780 --> 00:10:20.757 align:middle line:84%
And what I saw I
was so beautiful.

00:10:20.757 --> 00:10:21.715 align:middle line:90%
And I burst into tears.

00:10:21.715 --> 00:10:25.460 align:middle line:90%


00:10:25.460 --> 00:10:27.260 align:middle line:90%
And nothing else mattered.

00:10:27.260 --> 00:10:32.760 align:middle line:84%
I mean, in that moment,
just suddenly nothing

00:10:32.760 --> 00:10:41.600 align:middle line:84%
else mattered, except being
here, with this sacred river,

00:10:41.600 --> 00:10:48.410 align:middle line:84%
in this extraordinary,
exquisite truth, of my oneness

00:10:48.410 --> 00:10:56.420 align:middle line:84%
with God, whom I had just beheld
with every sense that I have.

00:10:56.420 --> 00:11:01.190 align:middle line:84%
Not just outside of
me, but inside of me.

00:11:01.190 --> 00:11:03.710 align:middle line:84%
And there was no distinction
between the inside

00:11:03.710 --> 00:11:05.840 align:middle line:90%
and the outside.

00:11:05.840 --> 00:11:10.230 align:middle line:84%
And it was-- all I could
say for so long was just,

00:11:10.230 --> 00:11:12.080 align:middle line:90%
oh, my god, it's so beautiful.

00:11:12.080 --> 00:11:14.240 align:middle line:90%
Oh, my god, it's so beautiful.

00:11:14.240 --> 00:11:17.760 align:middle line:90%
Oh, my god, it's so beautiful.

00:11:17.760 --> 00:11:25.280 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't know how, or where,
or why, or in what capacity.

00:11:25.280 --> 00:11:27.705 align:middle line:90%
And it didn't matter.

00:11:27.705 --> 00:11:29.080 align:middle line:84%
I just knew I'm
meant to be here.

00:11:29.080 --> 00:11:32.330 align:middle line:90%


00:11:32.330 --> 00:11:39.820 align:middle line:84%
And about-- and
a few days later,

00:11:39.820 --> 00:11:45.180 align:middle line:84%
I discovered the ashram where
I live, Parmarth Niketan,

00:11:45.180 --> 00:11:49.960 align:middle line:84%
has an alternate way of getting
from the hotel to the river.

00:11:49.960 --> 00:11:50.760 align:middle line:90%
It was clean.

00:11:50.760 --> 00:11:51.900 align:middle line:90%
It was beautiful.

00:11:51.900 --> 00:11:55.170 align:middle line:84%
The alleyway was not
so clean and beautiful.

00:11:55.170 --> 00:11:58.050 align:middle line:84%
And the ashram was just
exquisite, and gardens,

00:11:58.050 --> 00:12:01.750 align:middle line:84%
and beautiful statues-- and
again, I didn't know anything--

00:12:01.750 --> 00:12:05.520 align:middle line:84%
but just beautiful statues
and beautiful gardens.

00:12:05.520 --> 00:12:09.660 align:middle line:84%
And I'm walking through one
day, just walking from the river

00:12:09.660 --> 00:12:11.370 align:middle line:84%
back to the hotel, to
go to the bathroom.

00:12:11.370 --> 00:12:15.450 align:middle line:90%
And I hear a voice.

00:12:15.450 --> 00:12:19.200 align:middle line:84%
And the voice says
you must stay here.

00:12:19.200 --> 00:12:22.120 align:middle line:84%
I look around because clearly
if there was a voice someone

00:12:22.120 --> 00:12:22.920 align:middle line:90%
spoke.

00:12:22.920 --> 00:12:25.470 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't a welling
up of intuition.

00:12:25.470 --> 00:12:27.390 align:middle line:90%
People ask, well, what was it?

00:12:27.390 --> 00:12:28.470 align:middle line:90%
Was it a felt sense?

00:12:28.470 --> 00:12:31.230 align:middle line:90%
No, it was a voice.

00:12:31.230 --> 00:12:32.072 align:middle line:90%
Was it your voice?

00:12:32.072 --> 00:12:34.530 align:middle line:84%
Well, of course, it was my
voice because as you'll find out

00:12:34.530 --> 00:12:35.970 align:middle line:90%
there was no one else.

00:12:35.970 --> 00:12:41.360 align:middle line:84%
But it didn't speak
like my voice.

00:12:41.360 --> 00:12:42.840 align:middle line:90%
It was a man's voice.

00:12:42.840 --> 00:12:49.020 align:middle line:84%
It was an externally
perceived voice.

00:12:49.020 --> 00:12:51.720 align:middle line:90%
So I turn around.

00:12:51.720 --> 00:12:53.862 align:middle line:90%
And there's no one.

00:12:53.862 --> 00:12:55.320 align:middle line:84%
And then I figure
out, all right, I

00:12:55.320 --> 00:12:56.580 align:middle line:90%
guess I didn't hear a voice.

00:12:56.580 --> 00:12:58.060 align:middle line:90%
And didn't think much of it.

00:12:58.060 --> 00:12:59.610 align:middle line:90%
And kept walking.

00:12:59.610 --> 00:13:01.560 align:middle line:84%
And about 30 seconds
later, I hear it again.

00:13:01.560 --> 00:13:04.070 align:middle line:90%


00:13:04.070 --> 00:13:06.520 align:middle line:90%
You must stay here.

00:13:06.520 --> 00:13:07.820 align:middle line:90%
And again, I turned around.

00:13:07.820 --> 00:13:08.920 align:middle line:90%
And there's no one.

00:13:08.920 --> 00:13:13.272 align:middle line:84%
Look, is somebody shouting
from a balcony somewhere?

00:13:13.272 --> 00:13:15.210 align:middle line:90%
No one.

00:13:15.210 --> 00:13:17.330 align:middle line:84%
Now, in my entire
frame of reference

00:13:17.330 --> 00:13:20.180 align:middle line:84%
I was not even someone
who read spiritual books

00:13:20.180 --> 00:13:25.160 align:middle line:84%
or went to discourses
about spiritual people.

00:13:25.160 --> 00:13:27.950 align:middle line:84%
My whole frame of reference
of people who heard voices

00:13:27.950 --> 00:13:29.640 align:middle line:84%
were schizophrenics
and Joan of Arc.

00:13:29.640 --> 00:13:33.590 align:middle line:90%


00:13:33.590 --> 00:13:38.300 align:middle line:84%
And so I was just about
to ignore it again,

00:13:38.300 --> 00:13:43.800 align:middle line:84%
when what was very clearly my
own voice kicked in, and said,

00:13:43.800 --> 00:13:46.310 align:middle line:90%
OK, you can do that.

00:13:46.310 --> 00:13:48.770 align:middle line:84%
You can just pretend that
you've not heard a voice.

00:13:48.770 --> 00:13:50.780 align:middle line:90%
That's OK.

00:13:50.780 --> 00:13:53.220 align:middle line:90%
We understand.

00:13:53.220 --> 00:13:54.950 align:middle line:84%
But what that means
is that you're not

00:13:54.950 --> 00:13:57.870 align:middle line:90%
keeping your heart open.

00:13:57.870 --> 00:13:59.870 align:middle line:84%
And this is-- I mean, I
have these conversations

00:13:59.870 --> 00:14:00.680 align:middle line:90%
with myself.

00:14:00.680 --> 00:14:05.610 align:middle line:84%
I've always been very, very
deeply committed to truth,

00:14:05.610 --> 00:14:06.410 align:middle line:90%
from childhood.

00:14:06.410 --> 00:14:12.060 align:middle line:84%
That was-- that was my core
tenet, truth at all costs.

00:14:12.060 --> 00:14:20.527 align:middle line:84%
And so my inner voice says very
clearly, all right, go ahead.

00:14:20.527 --> 00:14:21.860 align:middle line:90%
Pretend you didn't hear a voice.

00:14:21.860 --> 00:14:22.700 align:middle line:90%
No problem.

00:14:22.700 --> 00:14:24.230 align:middle line:90%
We get it.

00:14:24.230 --> 00:14:27.770 align:middle line:84%
And you're going to have to turn
around and get yourself back

00:14:27.770 --> 00:14:30.638 align:middle line:84%
to Delhi, to get yourself
back on a flight to America,

00:14:30.638 --> 00:14:32.430 align:middle line:84%
because you're not
keeping your heart open.

00:14:32.430 --> 00:14:36.330 align:middle line:90%
And that was the value talking.

00:14:36.330 --> 00:14:38.910 align:middle line:84%
So you can pretend you
didn't hear a voice.

00:14:38.910 --> 00:14:42.730 align:middle line:84%
But you're not going
to go back on your vow.

00:14:42.730 --> 00:14:46.480 align:middle line:84%
And I was in the midst of these
days of just spiritual ecstasy.

00:14:46.480 --> 00:14:50.830 align:middle line:90%


00:14:50.830 --> 00:14:53.500 align:middle line:84%
I didn't want to
go back to Delhi.

00:14:53.500 --> 00:14:54.490 align:middle line:90%
We'd just gotten here.

00:14:54.490 --> 00:14:58.730 align:middle line:90%


00:14:58.730 --> 00:15:04.400 align:middle line:84%
And so I thought, all
right, I just heard a voice.

00:15:04.400 --> 00:15:05.390 align:middle line:90%
And I look up.

00:15:05.390 --> 00:15:09.610 align:middle line:84%
And I see a sign that
says, "Office" in English.

00:15:09.610 --> 00:15:10.700 align:middle line:90%
And I walk in.

00:15:10.700 --> 00:15:14.390 align:middle line:90%
And I say, I want to stay here.

00:15:14.390 --> 00:15:17.870 align:middle line:90%
And it's a long story.

00:15:17.870 --> 00:15:22.370 align:middle line:90%
But the end of the story--

00:15:22.370 --> 00:15:25.670 align:middle line:90%
fast forward about a week.

00:15:25.670 --> 00:15:31.880 align:middle line:84%
I finally am able to meet the
president, the head of Parmarth

00:15:31.880 --> 00:15:35.700 align:middle line:84%
Niketan, who, because
I had been told

00:15:35.700 --> 00:15:38.600 align:middle line:84%
they had to meet the
president, in my mind,

00:15:38.600 --> 00:15:40.760 align:middle line:84%
my mental construct
was president

00:15:40.760 --> 00:15:43.880 align:middle line:84%
means a gentleman in a suit,
and tie, and a briefcase,

00:15:43.880 --> 00:15:45.470 align:middle line:90%
and a desk.

00:15:45.470 --> 00:15:48.920 align:middle line:84%
And I had no idea that the
person I was about to meet it

00:15:48.920 --> 00:15:54.290 align:middle line:84%
was an enlightened
holy man, a revered--

00:15:54.290 --> 00:15:55.490 align:middle line:90%
revered religious leader.

00:15:55.490 --> 00:15:58.220 align:middle line:90%


00:15:58.220 --> 00:16:03.110 align:middle line:84%
And so when I finally,
finally met Pujya Swamiji,

00:16:03.110 --> 00:16:07.070 align:middle line:84%
it was as though he
were the glue that

00:16:07.070 --> 00:16:09.920 align:middle line:84%
brought all of the different
pieces of the experiences

00:16:09.920 --> 00:16:12.740 align:middle line:84%
I'd been having over the
previous week together.

00:16:12.740 --> 00:16:15.590 align:middle line:90%
And suddenly it made sense.

00:16:15.590 --> 00:16:20.270 align:middle line:84%
Suddenly I realized,
oh, yeah, it's here.

00:16:20.270 --> 00:16:22.610 align:middle line:90%
It's under him.

00:16:22.610 --> 00:16:27.920 align:middle line:84%
It's doing this type of work,
schools, and women's programs,

00:16:27.920 --> 00:16:34.620 align:middle line:84%
and health care, and
environment, and this service,

00:16:34.620 --> 00:16:38.160 align:middle line:84%
in this extraordinary
spiritually

00:16:38.160 --> 00:16:43.540 align:middle line:84%
open ecstasy that
I'm supposed to be.

00:16:43.540 --> 00:16:45.630 align:middle line:84%
And so suddenly
it all made sense.

00:16:45.630 --> 00:16:50.400 align:middle line:84%
And that was-- September,
it'll be 23 years.

00:16:50.400 --> 00:16:52.320 align:middle line:90%
And it's just been--

00:16:52.320 --> 00:16:53.370 align:middle line:90%
it's been extraordinary.

00:16:53.370 --> 00:16:58.680 align:middle line:84%
But circling back to the
beginning, its grace.

00:16:58.680 --> 00:17:01.020 align:middle line:90%
I was not a meditator.

00:17:01.020 --> 00:17:03.630 align:middle line:90%
I was not a spiritual seeker.

00:17:03.630 --> 00:17:07.859 align:middle line:84%
I was not someone who was
praying to God for a guru

00:17:07.859 --> 00:17:10.589 align:middle line:90%
or for the light.

00:17:10.589 --> 00:17:16.290 align:middle line:84%
And what I love about that is
grace doesn't discriminate.

00:17:16.290 --> 00:17:19.980 align:middle line:84%
Grace isn't saying,
you're worthy, you're not.

00:17:19.980 --> 00:17:23.339 align:middle line:84%
Grace isn't keeping some kind
of a tally of how many hours

00:17:23.339 --> 00:17:28.500 align:middle line:84%
you've spent meditating, how
many lustful or greedy thoughts

00:17:28.500 --> 00:17:31.290 align:middle line:90%
you've had.

00:17:31.290 --> 00:17:35.010 align:middle line:84%
You know, we put everything
kind of into this Santa Claus

00:17:35.010 --> 00:17:37.000 align:middle line:84%
analogy, of Santa Claus
knows you've been good,

00:17:37.000 --> 00:17:37.800 align:middle line:90%
you've been bad.

00:17:37.800 --> 00:17:40.230 align:middle line:84%
There's kind of this list,
the good girls, the bad girls,

00:17:40.230 --> 00:17:41.910 align:middle line:90%
the good boys, the bad boys.

00:17:41.910 --> 00:17:44.460 align:middle line:90%
And so we do that spiritually.

00:17:44.460 --> 00:17:47.270 align:middle line:90%


00:17:47.270 --> 00:17:50.870 align:middle line:90%
But that's not how grace works.

00:17:50.870 --> 00:17:56.120 align:middle line:90%
All grace needs is an opening.

00:17:56.120 --> 00:17:58.860 align:middle line:84%
And so that's why I
say, it's not my story.

00:17:58.860 --> 00:18:00.830 align:middle line:90%
It's grace's story.

00:18:00.830 --> 00:18:03.520 align:middle line:84%
I got picked up
and carried there.

00:18:03.520 --> 00:18:06.780 align:middle line:84%
There's one more piece
though that's just

00:18:06.780 --> 00:18:09.110 align:middle line:90%
a fun part of the story.

00:18:09.110 --> 00:18:16.880 align:middle line:84%
That after I met Pujya Swamiji
for the first time, I told him

00:18:16.880 --> 00:18:17.690 align:middle line:90%
I wanted to stay.

00:18:17.690 --> 00:18:20.630 align:middle line:84%
I didn't tell them
I had heard a voice.

00:18:20.630 --> 00:18:23.390 align:middle line:84%
I just told him
I wanted to stay.

00:18:23.390 --> 00:18:30.110 align:middle line:84%
And he says to me, this is your
home, stay whenever you like.

00:18:30.110 --> 00:18:32.470 align:middle line:90%
He says, I'm going away again.

00:18:32.470 --> 00:18:33.470 align:middle line:90%
He had been out of town.

00:18:33.470 --> 00:18:35.510 align:middle line:84%
He said, I'm going
out of town again.

00:18:35.510 --> 00:18:37.010 align:middle line:84%
But I'll be back
in about a week.

00:18:37.010 --> 00:18:39.290 align:middle line:84%
He said, but in any
case, don't worry.

00:18:39.290 --> 00:18:42.230 align:middle line:90%


00:18:42.230 --> 00:18:44.664 align:middle line:84%
I'll tell them to give
you a room anytime.

00:18:44.664 --> 00:18:48.460 align:middle line:90%


00:18:48.460 --> 00:18:51.140 align:middle line:84%
No, sorry-- he said, I'll
be here for about a week.

00:18:51.140 --> 00:18:53.335 align:middle line:84%
And then I'm going
out of town again.

00:18:53.335 --> 00:18:54.710 align:middle line:84%
We were heading
to the mountains.

00:18:54.710 --> 00:18:58.160 align:middle line:84%
So he said no problem, go to
the mountains if you want.

00:18:58.160 --> 00:19:00.440 align:middle line:84%
Even if I'm not here by
the time you get back,

00:19:00.440 --> 00:19:02.750 align:middle line:84%
I'll tell them to
give you a room.

00:19:02.750 --> 00:19:04.470 align:middle line:90%
You're always welcome.

00:19:04.470 --> 00:19:07.220 align:middle line:84%
And so I walk out of his
meeting area thinking,

00:19:07.220 --> 00:19:11.180 align:middle line:84%
OK, we'll go to the mountains
and stay when we come back.

00:19:11.180 --> 00:19:14.390 align:middle line:84%
And I get to this point in
the central part of the ashram

00:19:14.390 --> 00:19:17.870 align:middle line:84%
where we have this hand pump,
which is how most of India

00:19:17.870 --> 00:19:19.520 align:middle line:84%
traditionally has
always operated.

00:19:19.520 --> 00:19:20.728 align:middle line:90%
We've got this big hand pump.

00:19:20.728 --> 00:19:22.312 align:middle line:84%
We also have running
water, of course.

00:19:22.312 --> 00:19:24.410 align:middle line:84%
But nonetheless, we have
this beautiful hand pump,

00:19:24.410 --> 00:19:28.850 align:middle line:84%
that people actually
come from dozens of miles

00:19:28.850 --> 00:19:31.880 align:middle line:84%
away from, to get that
pure, beautiful water.

00:19:31.880 --> 00:19:37.130 align:middle line:84%
And I was about to turn
to walk out of the ashram.

00:19:37.130 --> 00:19:39.446 align:middle line:90%
And suddenly my feet won't walk.

00:19:39.446 --> 00:19:44.480 align:middle line:84%
I mean, literally my feet
are stuck to the ground.

00:19:44.480 --> 00:19:46.940 align:middle line:90%
And it felt like I--

00:19:46.940 --> 00:19:49.072 align:middle line:84%
like I was crazy-glued
to the ground.

00:19:49.072 --> 00:19:52.930 align:middle line:90%


00:19:52.930 --> 00:19:56.000 align:middle line:84%
And so initially I
think, oh, my god, I've

00:19:56.000 --> 00:19:57.530 align:middle line:84%
got some kind of
horrible disease.

00:19:57.530 --> 00:19:58.760 align:middle line:90%
I mean, I've got tetanus.

00:19:58.760 --> 00:19:59.660 align:middle line:90%
I've got polio.

00:19:59.660 --> 00:20:01.580 align:middle line:84%
I've got something
that I was supposed

00:20:01.580 --> 00:20:04.520 align:middle line:84%
to be vaccinated against and
the vaccination didn't work.

00:20:04.520 --> 00:20:07.155 align:middle line:90%


00:20:07.155 --> 00:20:08.780 align:middle line:84%
And then I come down
and I realize, all

00:20:08.780 --> 00:20:11.810 align:middle line:84%
right, chances are
lethal diseases

00:20:11.810 --> 00:20:14.810 align:middle line:90%
don't come on like this.

00:20:14.810 --> 00:20:17.090 align:middle line:84%
You were sitting on the
ground, on the floor, talking

00:20:17.090 --> 00:20:18.050 align:middle line:90%
to Swamiji.

00:20:18.050 --> 00:20:19.675 align:middle line:84%
You're not used to
sitting on the floor

00:20:19.675 --> 00:20:21.160 align:middle line:84%
or maybe your feet
are just asleep.

00:20:21.160 --> 00:20:24.830 align:middle line:84%
And so I bend down and I start
kind of massaging my legs.

00:20:24.830 --> 00:20:30.830 align:middle line:84%
And there's no pins or
needles, no tingling.

00:20:30.830 --> 00:20:32.870 align:middle line:90%
I can feel them fully.

00:20:32.870 --> 00:20:34.790 align:middle line:90%
They just don't move.

00:20:34.790 --> 00:20:38.700 align:middle line:84%
And so I close my eyes, and
I was studying neurology

00:20:38.700 --> 00:20:39.500 align:middle line:90%
at the time.

00:20:39.500 --> 00:20:40.520 align:middle line:90%
And so I close my eyes.

00:20:40.520 --> 00:20:45.260 align:middle line:84%
And I'm literally
picturing motor neurons

00:20:45.260 --> 00:20:46.610 align:middle line:90%
and they're firing.

00:20:46.610 --> 00:20:48.500 align:middle line:84%
And, OK, the right side
of the brain, and the

00:20:48.500 --> 00:20:49.445 align:middle line:90%
left side of the body.

00:20:49.445 --> 00:20:52.750 align:middle line:90%


00:20:52.750 --> 00:20:54.250 align:middle line:90%
Nothing.

00:20:54.250 --> 00:20:56.923 align:middle line:84%
And now you have to
picture me standing right

00:20:56.923 --> 00:20:58.090 align:middle line:90%
in the middle of the ashram.

00:20:58.090 --> 00:21:00.070 align:middle line:90%
My arms are kind of flailing--

00:21:00.070 --> 00:21:03.540 align:middle line:84%
flailing around
to get me to move.

00:21:03.540 --> 00:21:05.770 align:middle line:90%
Nothing.

00:21:05.770 --> 00:21:09.910 align:middle line:84%
So at that moment, from the
back gardens of the ashram,

00:21:09.910 --> 00:21:13.810 align:middle line:84%
this group of kids comes tearing
down the ashram path, just

00:21:13.810 --> 00:21:18.280 align:middle line:84%
playing tag, or some Indian
version of some kids' racing

00:21:18.280 --> 00:21:19.960 align:middle line:90%
game.

00:21:19.960 --> 00:21:22.850 align:middle line:84%
And instinctively, I
move backwards just

00:21:22.850 --> 00:21:24.500 align:middle line:90%
to get out of the way.

00:21:24.500 --> 00:21:26.310 align:middle line:84%
And then I realized,
oh, great, I'm free.

00:21:26.310 --> 00:21:29.120 align:middle line:90%
I can move.

00:21:29.120 --> 00:21:31.430 align:middle line:90%
And I can't.

00:21:31.430 --> 00:21:34.980 align:middle line:90%
My legs will not move forward.

00:21:34.980 --> 00:21:38.540 align:middle line:84%
And I then think, like a
good scientist, well, OK,

00:21:38.540 --> 00:21:40.940 align:middle line:90%
so I've just moved backwards.

00:21:40.940 --> 00:21:42.590 align:middle line:90%
I can't move forwards.

00:21:42.590 --> 00:21:45.020 align:middle line:84%
It means I've contracted
some disease whereby

00:21:45.020 --> 00:21:47.030 align:middle line:90%
I can only walk backwards.

00:21:47.030 --> 00:21:48.650 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:21:48.650 --> 00:21:51.440 align:middle line:84%
It had been sort of an
adventurous week anyway.

00:21:51.440 --> 00:21:53.720 align:middle line:90%
I decide I'll just spin around.

00:21:53.720 --> 00:21:55.250 align:middle line:90%
And I spin around.

00:21:55.250 --> 00:21:59.940 align:middle line:84%
And I'll walk out of
this ashram backwards.

00:21:59.940 --> 00:22:01.320 align:middle line:90%
So I spin around.

00:22:01.320 --> 00:22:04.910 align:middle line:84%
So now my back is
toward the exit

00:22:04.910 --> 00:22:12.050 align:middle line:84%
of the ashram, prepared to walk
backwards out of the ashram.

00:22:12.050 --> 00:22:13.230 align:middle line:90%
And my feet won't--

00:22:13.230 --> 00:22:14.030 align:middle line:90%
they won't move.

00:22:14.030 --> 00:22:16.640 align:middle line:84%
I cannot lift my
foot off the ground.

00:22:16.640 --> 00:22:20.480 align:middle line:90%


00:22:20.480 --> 00:22:23.690 align:middle line:84%
And I stop and I
realize, oh, my god, I

00:22:23.690 --> 00:22:25.490 align:middle line:84%
can't walk in that
direction at all,

00:22:25.490 --> 00:22:29.510 align:middle line:84%
not facing forward,
not facing backward.

00:22:29.510 --> 00:22:33.020 align:middle line:84%
But I had just moved
backwards, back

00:22:33.020 --> 00:22:35.180 align:middle line:84%
towards Swamiji's
room, when the kids had

00:22:35.180 --> 00:22:36.830 align:middle line:90%
come tearing around the bend.

00:22:36.830 --> 00:22:40.260 align:middle line:90%


00:22:40.260 --> 00:22:42.450 align:middle line:84%
And I was now facing
in that direction

00:22:42.450 --> 00:22:44.825 align:middle line:90%
because I had spun around.

00:22:44.825 --> 00:22:45.825 align:middle line:90%
And I thought, I wonder.

00:22:45.825 --> 00:22:48.690 align:middle line:90%


00:22:48.690 --> 00:22:52.560 align:middle line:84%
And I start walking
forward, no problem.

00:22:52.560 --> 00:22:55.330 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't whether I was facing
forward or facing backward.

00:22:55.330 --> 00:22:58.860 align:middle line:84%
It was whether I was trying
to walk out of the ashram

00:22:58.860 --> 00:23:00.750 align:middle line:90%
or stay in the ashram.

00:23:00.750 --> 00:23:02.250 align:middle line:90%
And so I walk back--

00:23:02.250 --> 00:23:07.187 align:middle line:84%
now no problem at all-- back
towards Pujya Swamiji's room.

00:23:07.187 --> 00:23:08.520 align:middle line:90%
And I walked back into the room.

00:23:08.520 --> 00:23:09.870 align:middle line:90%
Of course, it's full of people.

00:23:09.870 --> 00:23:12.390 align:middle line:90%
He's got open darshan going on.

00:23:12.390 --> 00:23:14.420 align:middle line:90%
I walked back in.

00:23:14.420 --> 00:23:16.170 align:middle line:90%
And I just stand in the doorway.

00:23:16.170 --> 00:23:18.110 align:middle line:90%
And he's meeting some people.

00:23:18.110 --> 00:23:20.310 align:middle line:84%
And after a few
moments, he looks up.

00:23:20.310 --> 00:23:23.070 align:middle line:84%
He doesn't look
surprised to see me,

00:23:23.070 --> 00:23:26.050 align:middle line:84%
maybe only three or four
minutes had passed anyway.

00:23:26.050 --> 00:23:32.060 align:middle line:84%
And I said to him, I think
I'm supposed to stay now.

00:23:32.060 --> 00:23:34.620 align:middle line:90%


00:23:34.620 --> 00:23:37.410 align:middle line:90%
And he says, welcome.

00:23:37.410 --> 00:23:38.210 align:middle line:90%
That was it.

00:23:38.210 --> 00:23:40.900 align:middle line:90%


00:23:40.900 --> 00:23:43.300 align:middle line:84%
>> And you stayed 23
years and counting.

00:23:43.300 --> 00:23:45.190 align:middle line:84%
>> I stayed 23
